++ Methods At-A-Glance

For direct-execution of commands, use...

* Solar_Sql::query()

To fetch rows, use ...

* Solar_Sql::select()

To quote values so they can be used safely in SQL commands, use ...

* Solar_Sql::quote()

* Solar_Sql::quoteInto()

* Solar_Sql::quoteMulti()

To conveniently manipulate data in individual tables, use...

* Solar_Sql::insert()

* Solar_Sql::update()

* Solar_Sql::delete()


For database-portable sequences, use...

* Solar_Sql::createSequence()

* Solar_Sql::dropSequence()

* Solar_Sql::nextSequence()


For database-portable transactions, use...

* Solar_Sql::begin()

* Solar_Sql::commit()

* Solar_Sql::rollback()

For database-portable table/column/index manipulation, use...

* Solar_Sql::createTable()

* Solar_Sql::dropTable()

* Solar_Sql::addColumn()

* Solar_Sql::dropColumn()

* Solar_Sql::createIndex()

* Solar_Sql::dropIndex()

